-- Westerwelle Sees Signals From Iran on Nuclear Talks, FT Deutschland Says
-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 2010-10-08T02:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/westerwelle-sees-signals-from-iran-on-nuclear-talks-ft-deutschland-says.html
German Foreign Minister  Guido Westerwelle  sees signals from Iran’s government that talks
concerning the country’s nuclear program could resume,  Financial
Times Deutschland  reported, citing an interview.  Westerwelle will discuss offering new talks with
International Atomic Energy Agency Director General  Yukiya Amano 
in Berlin today, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Cornelius Rahn  in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  